Privacy Policy
Last Updated: May 12, 2024
Introduction
SensusTech LLC ("we," "us," or "our") operates the mobile applications under our brand (the "Services"). This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and disclose your information when you use our Services.
Information We Collect
1. Advertising IDs and Device IDs:
We collect advertising IDs (e.g., Google Advertising ID) and device IDs (e.g., Android ID) to provide personalized ads and improve the user experience.
2. Usage Data and Analytics:
We collect data on how the Service is accessed and used. This includes information such as your deviceâ€™s Internet Protocol (IP) address, device type, operating system, the pages of our Service that you visit, the time and date of your visit, and other diagnostic data. We use third-party analytics tools to help us understand how users interact with our apps.
3. Crash Logs:
In the event of a crash, we collect crash logs that may include information about your device and the circumstances surrounding the crash. This data helps us identify and fix issues in our apps.
4. In-App Purchases:
If you make an in-app purchase, we collect information related to the purchase transaction, such as the item purchased, price, and transaction ID. We do not collect or store your payment information, which is handled by third-party payment processors.
How We Use Your Information
We use the collected data for various purposes:
To provide and maintain our Service.
To improve and personalize your experience.
To monitor the usage of our Service.
To detect, prevent, and address technical issues.
To show you advertisements that are relevant to you.
Sharing of Information
We may share your information with third-party service providers to facilitate our Service, provide the Service on our behalf, perform Service-related services, or assist us in analyzing how our Service is used. These third parties have access to your information only to perform these tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.
Security of Data
We take the security of your data seriously and use commercially acceptable means to protect it. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
Contact Us
